      "content": "i hear you on the age thing, but i'm looking at the presentation. the first guy is described as \"anxious\" and the second guy is \"agitated\". in a clinical setting, those can look really similar. isn't there a risk that we're just labeling the younger black male as \"agitated\" or a \"panic attack\" because of his appearance/clothing, while viewing the older white male's distress as a legitimate medical emergency? how do we make sure we aren't letting those descriptors bias the triage?",
